<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Students Continue Demonstrations Over Hebron </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1003152094 Cairo AL-'ARABI in Arabic 7 Mar 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> NC1003152094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-'ARABI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Hanan Kamal] </F>
  [Text] Angry demonstrations protesting the Hebron massacre 
have taken place in the Cairo universities for the second 
successive week. The demonstrations extended to regional 
universities, most notably Alexandria and al-Zaqaziq. In 
al-Zaqaziq University, the students of the Nasirist Ideology 
Club led a demonstration of thousands of students the day before 
yesterday protesting Arab inaction and the surrender of the PLO 
under 'Arafat. 
  Last Thursday, at Alexandria University, the security forces 
stormed the campus and used shotguns, tear gas canisters, and 
electric clubs [al-'usi al-kahraba'iyah] in an attempt to 
disperse thousands of student demonstrators, wounding over 100 
students, including eight who were taken to the university 
hospital and the Jamal 'Abd-al-Nasir Hospital. 

</TEXT>

