<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Saudi Arabia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Bans Use, Manufacturing of Satellite Dishes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1003154194 Riyadh Saudi Arabian Kingdom Radio Network in 
Arabic 1430 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1003154194 </F>
<F P=104>  Riyadh Saudi Arabian Kingdom Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The following decision has been issued by the 
Council of Ministers: 
  Decision No. 128, date 25/9/1414 A.H. [7/3/1994] 
  On the basis of the discussions in the Council of Ministers' 
session on the noticed constant increase in the spread of 
satellites which started to transmit their different TV programs 
to reception equipments wherever they might be. 
  In the interest of an organizational situation which 
determines the necessary controls and rules for the reception of 
external television broadcasts via the international satellite 
channels in the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia, the council decides the 
following: 
  First, the Information Ministry assumes the task and 
responsibility of implementing the project of receiving external 
television transmission via the international satellite channels 
and transmitting it to viewers via the cable system inside the 
kingdom in accordance with the religious and social values in 
the country. 
  Second, the import of dishes and their accessories which are 
used for the reception of foreign satellites programs is 
forbidden. The manufacturing of or any of their parts is 
forbidden inside the kingdom. The use of microwaves, decoders, 
or any other means for the reception and distribution of 
satellite transmission inside the kingdom is also banned. The 
manufacturing of the decoders or their parts is forbidden 
locally. 
  Third, it is forbidden to transfer satellite television 
transmission to the viewers inside the kingdom by anyone, or any 
quarter by means of subscriptions, be it by using microwaves, 
decoders, or anything else. 
  Fourth, whoever violates the provisions of articles 2 and 3 
of this decision is punishable by a financial fine of no less 
than 100,000 riyals and no more than 500,000 riyals, together 
with the confiscation of the equipments, the subject of the 
violation. 

</TEXT>

