<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Bid Receives Joint Committee, Urges Normalization </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1003181994 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1003181994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Last night in Aden, Brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid, vice 
chairman of the Presidential Council, received the members of 
the Joint Military Committee. Committee members briefed him on 
the progress of the committee's efforts to stop the 
deterioration and return military units to their previous 
positions, in accordance with the powers given to it to 
normalize the military situation and implement the provisions of 
the pledge and accord document pertaining to the military aspect. 
  Brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid welcomed the members of the Joint 
Military Committee and congratulated them on the end of the 
blessed month of Ramadan and the advent of the happy 'Id 
al-Fitr. He wished that the committee's efforts, as well as the 
positive results it has reached, will succeed in achieving all 
goals and missions. He stressed the need to speed up efforts to 
normalize the situation, remove all recently established 
military sites, and return units to their positions in order to 
end the tension that might spark sedition and fighting among the 
sons of the homeland. 
  The vice chairman of the Presidential Council stressed the 
need to double peaceful and democratic efforts and to resort to 
the spirit of dialogue, wisdom, rationality, patience, and 
perseverance to deal with all issues and challenges threatening 
the unity and efforts to build a modern Yemeni state. He 
emphasized the need to maintain unity, adhere to democracy, 
promote security and stability, and protect national and other 
interests under unity. 
  Concluding, brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid wished the committee 
every success in overcoming the difficulties and challenges and 
in preparing appropriate climates to continue its work to 
entrench the pillars of security and stability for our people 
and the region's peoples. 
  The meeting was attended by Defense Minister Staff Brigadier 
General Haytham Qasim Tahir. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

