<H3> <TI>   Talabani Visits Coalition Forces Office in Zakho </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1003184194 (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan 
in Arabic 1530 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1003184194 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan 
in Arabic 1530 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brother Jalal Talabani, secretary general of the 
Patriotic Union of Kurdistan [PUK], yesterday afternoon visited 
the coalition forces coordination office in Zakho. Talabani was 
accompanied by Dr. Fu'ad Ma'sum, member of the PUK Political 
Bureau; (Shaykh al-Hiwazi), alternate member of the Steering 
Committee; and (Shart al-Qazzaz), representative of the PUK in 
Ankara. The discussion during the visit dealt with the Iraqi 
regime's recent military movements near the border area of the 
Kurdistan region. The brother secretary general arrived in Dahuk 
yesterday evening. Brother Talabani returned to liberated 
Kurdistan the day before yesterday following a visit to Syria to 
attend the memorial service marking the 40th day since the death 
of Basil al-Asad, son of Syrian President Hafiz al-Asad. He met 
there with a number of Syrian officials and representatives of 
the national and Islamic forces in the Iraqi opposition based in 
Syria. 

</TEXT>

