<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Indictments Filed Against 3 for Supporting Massacre </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1103054794 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0500 GMT 11 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1103054794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Indictments have been filed in the Jerusalem 
Magistrate's Court against three Israelis who are accused of 
publicly supporting the Hebron massacre and expressing 
solidarity with Barukh Goldstein. The three are Shmu'el 
Ben-Yishay, Amnon Tadmor, and Arye Ben-Yosef. They are charged 
with violating the antiterrorism act. Shmu'el Ben-Yishay has 
already been under administrative detention for a week, and the 
High Court of Justice yesterday discussed a petition against the 
move. 

</TEXT>

