<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Settlers' Videocassette Recommends Civil Revolt </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1003161594 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 1500 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1003161594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The distress of Judaea and Samaria settlers is 
being handled by the Action Committee for the Annulment of the 
Autonomy Plan, which is currently disseminating a videocassette 
encouraging civil revolt. The tape recommends evading military 
service and not paying taxes as a means of opposing the 
government's policy. Yiftah El'azar reports: 
  The hero of the videocassette is an imaginary character 
called Ron Segev, a tank brigade commander, and deals with his 
misgivings under the autonomy. Segev is detained by a joint 
patrol of the Palestinian police and the Israeli Border Police 
while demonstrating against Yasir 'Arafat's arrival in East 
Jerusalem. Segev decides to become a prisoner of conscience and 
inspires others to follow in his footsteps. Elyaqim Ha'etzni, 
head of the action committee, hopes that in real life Israelis 
will turn to civil revolt. 
  [Begin Ha'etzni recording] It is a path of non-violence 
aimed at opposing a regime which almost clandestinely -- we call 
it the Oslo underground -- surprised and hoodwinked the nation, 
and with the help of pro-PLO votes in the Knesset, is taking the 
country away from the people. It is a path of nonviolence. 
[end recording] 
  The cassette contains the names of right-wing intellectuals, 
such as Professor Yisra'el Eldad and Prof. Hilel Weiss, as well 
as senior military commanders in the reserves, who support the 
action. Among the measures recommended are dodging military 
reserve duty and evading the payment of taxes. Ha'etzni said it 
is important to learn how to carry out civil revolt in order to 
prevent a repetition of actions like that of Barukh Goldstein, 
who perpetrated the Hebron massacre. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

