<H3> <TI>   Poll: Rabin Public's Choice for Prime Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1103115794 Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT in Hebrew 11 Mar 94 p 
1 </F>

<F P=103> TA1103115794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A public opinion poll conducted by the Dahaf 
Institute directed by Dr. Mina Tzemah posed the following 
question: In your opinion, who is best suited to be prime 
minister today? 
  Yitzhaq Rabin -- 44 percent; Binyamin Netanyahu -- 22 
percent; Refa'el Eytan -- 12 percent; none of them -- 20 
percent; did not reply -- 2 percent. 
  The poll was conducted on 9 March among 507 respondents who 
constitute a representative sample of the adult population of 
Israel. The maximum margin of error is 4 percent. 

</TEXT>

