that the Israeli Government cancel it. 
  [Darawshah] We used the phrase "having reservations." This 
is the ?(view) of Palestinians inside Israel. The majority of 
the political forces, including the Arab Democratic Party, 
welcomed the Oslo agreement as an agreement of principle, hoping 
that this would be (?followed) by a detailed agreement ensuring 
Palestinian rights. However, Israel's attempt to obtain big 
gains from the Palestinian side without offering real 
concessions made us express reservations over the Cairo 
agreement, without expressing opposition. We have reservations. 
[passage omitted] 

