<H3> <TI>   Damascus Denies Claims of Threats to Syrian Jews </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0803113594 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 6 Mar 94 p3 </F>
<F P=103> PM0803113594 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Repot by Salwa al-Ustuwani: "Syria Denies Jews Threatened"] </F>
  [Excerpt] Damascus -- Syria yesterday denied the claims 
made by an American Jewish organization alleging that threats 
were made against Syrian Jews after the al-Ibrahimi mosque 
massacre on 25 February. It accused Israel of being behind such 
deceptive lies. 
  In the first comment on reports about a message received by 
Syrian Jews from sources claiming to belong to the Syrian 
Islamic Party for Justice and saying that it is permissible to 
spill Jewish blood, a Syrian official said that no such name 
exists at all. 
  He added that the claims by American Jewish organizations 
that Jews in Syria were threatened and are facing the danger of 
revenge for the Hebron massacre, and the crocodile tears shed 
for the Jews of Syria by Israel and its Jewish organizations, 
from whom the American Jewish organizations get their orders, 
are all part of the continuous attempts to confuse and cast 
doubt on the situation in Syria and on the Syrian position 
advocating a just, comprehensive, and lasting peace. 
  The Syrian official said that Israel knows very well that it 
would only reap failure and that it would never be able to 
absolve itself of the crimes it commits in broad daylight 
against Arab citizens and holy places. 
  He accused Israel of always trying to force Arab Jews to 
immigrate to it, and then committing massacres against them to 
force them to commit massacres. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

