<F P=102>  NC1103104294 Paris AFP in English 0944 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1103104294 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, March 11 (AFP) -- A man threw two petrol 
bombs into the Syrian Embassy courtyard in the Iranian capital 
on Thursday, but caused no injuries or damage, Syrian diplomats 
in Tehran said Friday. 
  The assailant, suspected to be deranged, was arrested and 
Iranian authorities opened an inquiry into the attack, the 
diplomats said without giving more details. 

