<H3> <TI>   Rabin Tours `Occupied' Border Area, Meets Lahd </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0903175094 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1630 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0903175094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Before we get into details of the news, we would 
like to note a new Israeli move that falls in the context of the 
continuous defiance and provocations the Hebrew state indulges 
in against Lebanese sovereignty. 
  The enemy's prime minister, Yitzhaq Rabin, today toured the 
occupied border region. He met in Marj 'Uyun barracks with 
Antoine Lahd, commander of the agent militia, and a number of 
his military commanders. 
  Radio Voice of the South, the mouthpiece of Lahd's South 
Lebanese Army, carried a statement by Rabin in which he 
insinuated that peace with Lebanon will come after the 
resistance is eliminated, particularly Hizballah; after the 
Lebanese Government proves its ability to maintain security 
north of the border area for six months; and after the soldiers 
and officers of Lahd's militia are absorbed in the Lebanese 
Army, as Rabin put it. 

