<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Inter-Arab Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Arab League Chief Recieves Croatian Ambassador </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1003140794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1140 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1003140794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 10 Mar (MENA)--Arab League Secretary General 
Dr. 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid today received Croatian Ambassador 
Danijel Bucan. 
  After the meeting Bucan said that he discussed with Dr. 
'Abd-al-Majid the agreement concluded by Bosnia-Herzegovina's 
Muslims and Croats to establish a confederal union with Croatia 
so that the Muslim-Croatian "canton" would become an independent 
state, but at the same time linked to Croatia in matters of 
joint defense, markets, and a customs union. 
  He added that he sensed during his talks with Dr. 
'Abd-al-Majid that the latter shares his view that the agreement 
is essential to a peaceful solution of the war in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina and the general crisis in the former 
Yugoslavia. 
  The Croatian ambassador said he expects the agreement to 
succeed in view of the longstanding friendship between Muslims 
and Catholics in that region. He referred to the existence of a 
mosque and Islamic center in Croatia. 
  Bucan said he hopes Russia will play a positive role in 
ensuring the agreement's success. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

