<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yemen's al-Bid Says Fahd Welcomed King's Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1203200994 Kuwait AL-RA'Y AL-'AMM in Arabic 10 Mar 94 pp 
1, 19 </F>

<F P=103> JN1203200994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait AL-RA'Y AL-'AMM </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Contrary to the expectations that had spread in the 
Jordanian capital, King Husayn left Saudi Arabia without being 
received by the custodian of the two holy mosques. 
  Jordanian sources had said that while in Saudi Arabia, the 
king would hold talks on the Gulf situation, clearing the Arab 
atmosphere, and peace efforts. 
  AL-RA'Y AL-'AMM has learned from its special sources that 
the 
idea of the Jordanian king's visit to Saudi Arabia had been 
proposed by Yemeni Vice President 'Ali Salim al-Bid in Saudi 
Arabia during his meeting with the custodian of the two holy 
mosques, who welcomed the accord document signed in Amman. The 
sources said that al-Bid telephoned King Husayn in the presence 
of the custodian of the two holy mosques, who welcomed the 
king's visit for minor pilgrimage. 

</TEXT>

