<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> United Arab Emirates </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yemen President Holds Talks With Zayid </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1103213494 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
2000 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1103213494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah 
Salih, chairman of the Presidential Council, and His Highness 
Shaykh Zayid Bin-Sultan Al Nuhayyan, president of the United 
Arab Emirates [UAE], have held a closed session at al-Musharraf 
Palace in Abu Dhabi. 
  The Yemeni News Agency, SABA, has learned that the two 
presidents discussed issues and developments of interest to the 
relations between the two brotherly countries and ways of 
enhancing them. They also discussed developments in the Arab 
arena and the efforts of the two fraternal countries to restore 
Arab solidarity. 
  During the meeting, the brother president briefed his 
brother, His Highness Shaykh Zayid Bin-Sultan, on developments 
in Yemen in light of the signing of the accord document and the 
efforts under way to contain the political crisis in our 
country. He also briefed him on the successes by the joint 
military committee in stopping the regrettable military 
developments. He further expressed his appreciation for the 
brothers, including the brothers in the UAE, for their support 
for our people ini overcoming the challenges imposed by the 
political crisis and their support for Yemeni unity. 
  Brother Lt. Gen. 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih arrived in Abu Dhabi 
at 
2100 Sanaa local time today leading a high-level delegation on a 
brotherly visit to the fraternal UAE. He is to meet with his 
brother, His Highness Shaykh Zayid Bin-Sultan Al Nuhayyan, 
president of the UAE, for talks on fraternal relations and ways 
of enhancing them. They will also discuss developments in the 
regional, Arab, and international arenas, as well as issues of 
interest to our Arab nation, primarily ways to clear the Arab 
atmosphere and restore Arab solidarity, and issues of common 
interest. The brother president will also brief his brother, 
His Highness Shaykh Zayid Bin-Sultan, on the developments in our 
country and the efforts being made to contain the current 
political crisis and implement the accord document. The purpose 
of this is to end the crisis, safeguard unity and democracy, and 
bolster stability in our country. 
  His Highness Shaykh Zayid Bin-Sultan Al Nuhayyan, president 
of the UAE, led those who received the brother chairman of the 
Presidential Council at Abu Dhabi Airport. He gave the brother 
chairman a warm brotherly hug and welcomed him. [passage 
omitted] 
  Upon arrival at Abu Dhabi Airport, the brother chairman of 
the Presidential Council made a statement to the UAE mass media. 
He said: Our visit to the sisterly UAE tonight gives me 
personally an opportunity to meet with dear brother His Highness 
Shakyh Zayid Bin-Sultan Al-Nuhayyan, the UAE president, and to 
hold consultations with him on all that is related to the 
intimate relations between the two sisterly countries. These 
distinguished relations are testified to by the projects that 
have been carried out by the UAE in Yemen, projects that prove 
the deep relations of amity among the peoples of the Arabian 
Peninsula and the Gulf. Our Yemeni people will always highly 
appreciate the stand of Shaykh Zayid and the sons of his 
generous people in the UAE and their contribution to our 
development process and support for the unity of Yemen. [words 
indistinct] a living example of the deep sisterly relations 
between the two peoples. During the visit, I will brief my 
honorable brother, Shaykh Zayid, on the developments of the 
situation in our country in light of the signing of the pledge 
and accord document and the efforts being exerted to begin 
implementing it on the basis of reviving the Constitutional and 
executive institutions and cooperation among all parties to the 
government coalition -- the General Peoples's Congress, the 
Yemeni Socialist Party, and the Yemeni Reform Grouping. This 
will ensure putting an end to the political crisis, containing 
its regrettable repercussions, consolidating unity, and 
maintaining the democratic experience in our country. In this 
regard, we cannot do without the efforts and role of the 
brothers in the UAE, led by His Shaykh Zayid Bin-Sultan, who has 
taken honorable pan-Arab stands in support of Yemeni unity, 
which is a pan-Arab gain for the Arab nation and a significant 
factor for bolstering regional security, stability, and peace. 
We are also looking forward to a greater UAE role at the 
current stage in view of the his Highness Shaykh Zayid's special 
status in the hearts of the sons of Yemen and for his known 
wisdom and pan-Arab concern to serve the Arab nation's 
objectives and supreme interests. Undoubtedly, our talks in the 
UAE will deal with ways of clearing the Arab atmosphere of all 
impurities that have stuck to it as a result of the regrettable 
Gulf crisis. We will also be discussing ways of restoring Arab 
solidarity, especially since His Highness Shaykh Zayid initiated 
the call for healing the rift, closing Arab ranks, and restoring 
Arab solidarity. We in the Republic of Yemen have supported 
this pan-Arab initiative. We will do our best along with our 
brothers to achieve this objective. 

</TEXT>

