<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister To Ask Cabinet To Meet in Aden </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1203071994 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2150 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1203071994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 11 Mar (MENA)--Yemeni Prime Minister Engineer 
Haydar Abu-Bakr al-'Attas has announced that he will address a 
final invitation to the cabinet to meet in Aden after the 'Id 
al-Fitr holiday to discuss ways to implement the Pledge and 
Accord Document that was signed in Jordan and has not been 
implemented yet. 
  In an interview with AL-AHRAM's Saturday edition, he said an 
invitation will also be sent to the National Dialogue Committee 
to meet in Aden after the 'Id al-Fitr holiday to continue the 
dialogue, which stopped after a number of its participants 
withdrew because of escalating squabbles, the mass media's 
stand, and military clashes between the armed forces of the 
General People's Congress in Sanaa and the Socialist Party's 
forces in the border governorates in Abyan, Abb, (Ta'izz), and 
Lahij. 
  He expressed hopes that the crisis will be resolved and 
noted 
the need for all the parties to cooperate to achieve this end. 
  Al-'Attas emphasized that terrorism has serious effects on 
Yemen and on the Arab countries to which this terrorism is 
exported. He said he does not approve of any terrorist act 
directed from his country at fraternal Egypt or other Arab 
countries. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

