<H3> <TI>   Muslim Fundamentalists Escape in Mass Jail Break </TI></H3>
<H4>   Prime Minister Orders Inquiry </H4>
<F P=102> NC1203190194 Cairo ESC Television in Arabic 1800 GMT 12 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1203190194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo ESC Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Redha Malek has decided to form an 
inquiry commission into an incident that involved an armed 
attack on an Algerian prison yesterday during which more than 
400 [as heard] prisoners escaped. Some members of the country's 
armed Islamic movements, who faced the death penalty, were among 
the escapees. 
  The Algerian security forces are continuing to comb the area 
surrounding the prison to search for the escaped convicts and 
the gunmen who carried out the attack. 
  Four prison guards were killed in the attack. 

</TEXT>

