<H3> <TI>   Muslim Fundamentalists Escape in Mass Jail Break </TI></H3>
<H4>   Security Forces Capture 79, Kill 24 </H4>
<F P=102> LD1403143094 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 1400 
GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1403143094 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The security services today announced that 79 of the 
prisoners who escaped from Tazoult prison last Thursday evening 
have been recaptured, while 24 others have been killed by the 
security forces which have retrieved several weapons. 
  A statement by the security services adds that the search 
and 
surrounding operations are continuing. On the other hand, the 
Ministry of Interior and Local Authorities announces to the 
citizens residing in the privinces of Algiers, Blida, Boumerdes, 
Medea, Tipaza, Ain Defla, Bouira, Djelfa, Msila, and Chelef that 
from tomorrow night the curfew hours will be from 2330 to 0400. 

</TEXT>

