<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Aziz Visit to UN Reportedly `Postponed' to 15 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1203193394 Amman Jordan Television Network in Arabic 1800 
GMT 12 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1203193394 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Jordan Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The visit which Iraqi Deputy Prime Minister Tariq 
'Aziz was expected to pay to the UN headquarters in New York 
today has been postponed until 15 March. The purpose of the 
visit is to hold a new round of talks on removing Iraqi weapons 
of mass destruction. 
  Lieutenant General 'Amir Rashid, head of Iraq's Military 
Industrialization Organization; and Riyad al-Qaysi, Iraqi 
Foreign Ministry under secretary, are scheduled to join these 
talks. A UN source said the first round of talks which 'Aziz 
will hold with Ambassador Rolf Ekeus, head of the UN commission 
in charge of destroying the Iraqi arms arsenal, will be held on 
Wednesday. 

</TEXT>

