<H3> <TI>   Envoy to Israel on Need To Remove All Settlements </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1403071994 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0600 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1403071994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 14 Mar (MENA)--Egyptian Ambassador in Israel 
Muhammad Basyuni has stressed Egypt's insistence on the need for 
international supervision to protect the Palestinians in the 
occupied territories to prevent the repetition of the incident 
in Hebron. 
  In an interview with AL-AHRAM today, Monday, he noted that 
Egypt's stand on the settlement policy is clear and known and 
that it considers the settlements illegal and that they should 
all be removed. He remarked that there is agreement to discuss 
the matter in the final stages of the solution. 
  He expressed his belief that the Israeli-Palestinian talks 
will not be resumed officially until the Security Council passes 
a resolution denouncing the Hebron operation and providing 
protection for the Palestinians. 
  The ambassador denounced Israeli and Western media 
exaggerations and one-upmanship in handling the manifestations 
of violence and terrorism in Egypt and these media's attempts to 
damage Egypt's image abroad. 

</TEXT>

