<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gunmen Attack Christian Monastery Near al-Qusiyah </TI></H3>
<H4>   Investigation Begins </H4>
<F P=102> NC1103224394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2212 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1103224394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 11 Mar (MENA)--Four people died and three 
others were wounded this evening when unidentified gunmen fired 
in the direction of the gate of al-Muharraq Monastery in 
al-Qusiyah, Asyut Governorate, and escaped. 
  A responsible security source at the Interior Ministry said 
that at about 1830 today, unidentified men fired at the gate of 
al-Muharraq Monastery in al-Qusiyah, 45 km north of Asyut in 
Upper Egypt. The source added that Safwat Sami Shawqi, a 
13-year-old student; Najib Sa'id Yunan, a 30-year-old employee 
of Ghabbur Company; Sayf Shafiq Sayf, a 23-year-old peasant; and 
the monastery's priest Nur-al-Qums Binyamin, 45, died as a 
result. 
  The source said the three wounded people were taken to 
al-Qusiyah Hospital for treatment. 
  Officials of the Asyut Security Directorate, the Public 
Security Authority, the Criminology Investigation Department, 
and the Criminology Laboratory went to the scene of the incident 
to investigate. The area is being searched and ambushes are 
being set to arrest the culprits. The prosecution has been 
informed to begin an investigation. 

</TEXT>

