<H3> <TI>   Gunmen Attack Christian Monastery Near al-Qusiyah </TI></H3>
<H4>   Archbishop Says Incident `Isolated' </H4>
<F P=102> NC1203150794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1325 GMT 12 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1203150794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Asyut, 12 Mar (MENA)--Anba Saverios, archbishop of 
al-Muharraq Monastery in al-Qusiyah, has stated that the 
shooting at the monastery yesterday was an isolated incident 
intended to grab media headlines, strike at national unity, and 
divide the nation's two communities. 
  In an exclusive statement to MENA, the archbishop said the 
incident will have no effect on the relations between Muslims 
and Christians but will make them more determined to adhere to 
national unity. 
  On the circumstances of the incident, he said that at 
approximately 1800 yesterday, a citizen accompanied by his 
relatives arrived in a car to visit the monastery. The head of 
the monastery apologized to them because they could not enter 
the monastery during the period of fasting. He added that while 
the car's passengers were standing outside the monastery, 
unknown people opened fire at the car and its passengers. He 
added that 27 empty cartridges fired from an automatic weapon 
were found at the scene of the incident. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

