<H3> <TI>   Gunmen Fire on Nile Tourist Boat Near Asyut </TI></H3>
<H4>   AFP Reports No Injuries </H4>
<F P=102> NC1303110594 Paris AFP in English 0928 GMT 13 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1303110594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Lamia Radi] </F>
  [excerpt] Asyut, Egypt, March 13 (AFP) -- Gunmen shot at 14 
Britons on a Nile cruise after dawn on Sunday but no-one was 
hurt, in the latest of several weekend attacks by suspected 
Islamic militants that killed two priests and six other people. 
  Police escorting the Royal Rhapsody cruise boat fired back 
but the gunmen escaped along the Nile River near the Islamic 
militant stronghold of Asyut, 360 kilometers (216 miles) south 
of Cairo, security services said. 
  The tourists were sailing from Suhaj to the capital Cairo. 
  For the past year police have escorted tour boats in rubber 
dinghies in a broad effort to protect tourists targeted by 
militants seeking to sabotage the Egyptian economy and bring 
down the secular government. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

