<H3> <TI>   Newspapers View Failure To Pass Hebron Resolution </TI></H3>
<H4>   U.S. Urged To Be Impartial </H4>
<F P=102> NC1403080794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0607 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1403080794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 14 Mar (MENA)--AL-AKHBAR newspaper calls on 
the international community to face up to its political, 
humanitarian, and moral responsibility by reaching a decisive 
and clear resolution on the brutal crime of the al-Ibrahimi 
Mosque perpetrated by Israeli extremism under the sponsorship of 
Israeli military and civilian leaders. 
  In an editorial written by its chief editor today, Monday, 
the paper says that the Security Council's failure to pass a 
resolution of denunciation during the past two weeks is 
repulsive and indicates that the aim is to contain the 
revolution of world public opinion against the brutal measures 
against the Palestinian people. 
  The paper calls on the United States to act as a fair judge, 
to stop being partial, and adhere to moral and humanitarian 
principles in its international dealing if it is serious in 
truly playing the role of superpower in today's world. 
  The paper emphasizes that a clear vision of the flagrant 
aggression being suffered by the Palestinians will contribute to 
the resumption of the peace process in an atmosphere of trust 
until an agreement recovering the legitimate Palestinian Arab 
rights is reached. Thus, the paper concludes, the hope for a 
fair world order guaranteeing security and stability for all 
states and nations can materialize. 

</TEXT>

