<H4>   States Willingness To Hand Over Suspects </H4>
<F P=102> NC1203083594 (Clandestine) Radio Free Lebanon in Arabic 0545 
GMT 12 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1203083594 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Free Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Lebanese Forces Commander Dr. Samir Ja'ja' said in a 
telephone interview with the London-based AL-HAYAH newspaper 
that he does not know the reasons behind the tightened measures 
still being taken by units of the Lebanese Army in Ghidras. 
Ja'ja' expressed his willingness to hand over any wanted person 
if investigations prove he had a connection with recent 
explosions. 
  Stating that the state, with all its apparatuses, has not 
requested he hand over anyone, Ja'ja' said: We were surprised 
by these measures, for which I can find no explanation. 
  Ja'ja' revealed that 20 people have been arrested and that a 
100 members of the Lebanese Forces are being treated as suspects 
and are being harassed. 

