<H3> <TI>   Fadlallah: Church Blast To `Divert' Lebanese </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1103140594 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 1215 GMT 11 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1103140594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Voice of Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] 'Allamah Sayyid Muhammad Husayn Fadlallah believes 
that the Sayyidat al-Najat explosion was meant to be a mine 
undercutting the Lebanese people, because what was required was 
to create a limited security threat that would then be turned 
into a political earthquake to divert the attention of the 
people from economic issues to concentrate on security matters. 
  He said violating security harms both Christians and 
Muslims. 
He noted that whoever throws a bomb at a church will also do 
the same to a mosque. Whoever places a bomb near a cultural 
center somewhere will also place it in a cultural center here. 

</TEXT>

