<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Qaddumi: U.S. `Obstacle' to UN Resolution </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1303114994 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1005 GMT 13 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1303114994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tunis, 13 Mar (MENA)--PLO Political Department Chief 
Faruq Qaddumi has said that it is impossible for the 
Palestinians to return to the peace negotiations without a 
Security Council resolution providing for international 
protection for the Palestinian people in the occupied 
territories and without tangible, concrete measures on the 
ground to reassure the Palestinian people. 
  He told the Tunisian newspaper AL-SABAH today that the 
United 
States remains an obstacle in the way of such a resolution. 
Washington is asking the PLO to resume negotiations with Israel, 
although it knows that this is impossible without a Security 
Council resolution. 
  Qaddumi accused the current team at the U.S. State 
Department 
of being biased and sympathetic toward Israel and trying to 
extort the Palestinian people, as he put it. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

