<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sources `Believe' Talks To Resume 21 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1303153194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1500 GMT 13 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1303153194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The negotiations between Israel and the PLO will 
apparently resume on next Monday, 21 March. Palestinian sources 
told our correspondent Moti Amir that this date was proposed to 
Yasir 'Arafat and Yitzhaq Rabin by U.S. officials. 
  The sources believe that agreement was reached on this 
issue. 
The talks will resume in Washington and in Paris. The sources 
told our correspondent that the PLO's agreement to renew the 
negotiations was made conditional on the Security Council's 
resolution regarding the Hebron massacre, and was given after 
Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin promised the Americans that the 
negotiations, as well as Israel's redeployment in the Gaza Strip 
and Jericho, would be completed before 14 April. 

</TEXT>

