<H3> <TI>   Al-Husayni Welcomes Israeli Cabinet Decision on Kakh </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1303184194 Jerusalem New Channel 2 Television Network in 
Hebrew 1800 GMT 13 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1303184194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem New Channel 2 Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Palestinians have welcomed the cabinet's 
decision on Kakh and Kahana Hay, but stressed that its test will 
lie in its enforcement on the ground. According to Faysal 
al-Husayni, one of the PLO leaders in the territories, the 
decision is not enough to return the Palestinians to the 
negotiations table. 
  [Begin al-Husayni recording, in English] If it will be 
followed by all of the steps that we were talking about and 
asking for, like evacuating the settlers from the heart of 
al-Khalil [Hebron], from Gaza, I believe this will help starting 
fruitful negotiations. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

