<H3> <TI>   Quray': Israeli Cabinet Decision `Not Enough' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1303190994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Arabic 1555 GMT 13 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1303190994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report on interview with Ahmad Quray', head of the PLO </F>
Economic Department, by Qol Yisra'el correspondent Sa'd Mu'addi, 
on 13 March; place not given; from the "With the Events" program] 
  [Text] Commenting on the government's decision to outlaw 
Kakh, Kahana Hay, PLO Economic Department head Ahmad Quray', 
also known as Abu-al-'Ala' had the following to say: 
  [Begin Quray' recording] Certainly, it is a good step in the 
right direction. But it is not enough. It does not come 
anywhere near equaling the crime that has been committed. A 
more substantial solution should be sought so an appropriate 
atmosphere is created for the resumption of negotiations. 
Measures must be taken around the Ibrahimi Mosque and the 
locations of settlers. That is what we had expected. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

