<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   DFLP Statements on Border Raid Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1203190994 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran in 
Arabic 1730 GMT 12 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1203190994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Muhammad Bishqar in Beirut] </F>
  [Text] Palestinian mujahidin launched a major attack on a 
Zionist settlement in northern occupied Palestine today. 
Subsequent extensive clashes between the mujahidin and the 
Zionist forces left a large number of the latter dead or wounded. 
  The Nayif Hawatimah-led Democratic Front for the Liberation 
of Palestine [DFLP] issued three successive statements in Beirut 
this afternoon, claiming responsibility for the attack. It 
reported that one of its groups infiltrated occupied Palestinian 
territory via south Lebanon and attacked a Zionist settlement. 
Several hours of fierce fighting with the Zionist occupation 
forces followed, during which the DFLP fighters killed or 
injured a large number of enemy troops. 
  The DFLP statements asserted that one of its fighters, who 
was in charge of maintaining communications from south Lebanon 
with the other group members, was arrested by the UN Interim 
Force in Lebanon [UNIFIL]. The DFLP demanded his immediate 
release. 
  According to earlier reports from south Lebanon, two 
Palestinian martyrs fell during fighting with the occupation 
forces today and a third was captured by the enemy. A fourth 
was arrested by UNIFIL's Norwegian contingent. 
  This afternoon the Zionist occupation forces bombarded and 
raked with heavy machine-gun fire liberated villages in the 
eastern sector of the southern border belt, including Dallafah, 
Qilya, Zummarayya, and Jabal al-Dahr. 
  Meanwhile, the Islamic Resistance addressed a new warning 
this afternoon to the agents serving in Antoine Lahd's militia 
[South Lebanese Army, SLA] that it will punish all of them 
sooner or later. 
  The warning added that the enemy Prime Minister Yitzhaq 
Rabin's visit to south Lebanon to reassure the agents and all 
the financial and military assistance given to them will not 
save them from the mujahidin. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

