<H3> <TI>   DFLP, PFLP Command Still Wants 'Arafat Out </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1203180494 Damascus SANA in Arabic 1550 GMT 12 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN1203180494 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus SANA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Damascus, 12 Mar (SANA)--The unified command of the 
Democratic Front for the Liberation of Palestine [DFLP] and the 
Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine [PFLP] has 
condemned the U.S. role which is obstructing the Security 
Council's role by preventing it from adopting a resolution 
condemning Israel for the barbaric massacre it perpetrated in 
the holy al-Ibrahimi Mosque. 
  In a statement issued today, the command said that PLO 
Chairman Yasir 'Arafat's retreat from demanding international 
protection for the Palestinians, the dismantlement of 
settlements in the occupied Arab territories, and evacuation of 
settlers is a new violation of the Palestinian national 
consensus that negotiations with Israel should be stopped. 
  In its statement, the command said that it renews its call 
for 'Arafat's resignation as a necessary step to learn lessons 
from the Israeli massacre and to maintain Palestinians' national 
rights. 

</TEXT>

