<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Affirms Commitment to Palestinians' Security </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1303153494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1500 GMT 13 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1303153494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Due to the spate of reports pertaining to the IDF's 
[Israel Defense Forces] rules of engagement in the territories 
and in the wake of the Hebron massacre, the cabinet today 
adopted a resolution reiterating the Israeli Government's 
responsibility, through the IDF and the police, for the security 
of all the residents of the territories, both Jews and Arabs. 
  The cabinet reiterated its commitment to provide maximum 
security for all the residents of the territories. The 
resolution stated that the IDF and the security forces had been 
instructed to exhaust all legal and security measures in order 
to fulfill this goal. 
  The cabinet's resolution stipulated that the Palestinian 
police would be responsible for the security of Palestinian 
residents in the areas it was deployed in. Until the 
Palestinian police was established, Israel would take all 
necessary measures to prevent any security vacuum. 

</TEXT>

