<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Two IDF Generals Empowered To Define `Terrorist' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1303202594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 2000 GMT 13 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1303202594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The commanders of the IDF's [Israel Defense Forces] 
Central and Southern Commands today signed an order empowering 
them to define any group employing violence and threats as a 
terrorist organization. This expands the authority of the two 
major generals responsible for the areas where most of the Kakh 
and Kahana Hay members reside. 
  Up until now, the Antiterror Act could only be enforced 
inside the Green Line and had no legal validity in the 
territories. If the IDF commanders make use of their new 
powers, it will be possible to take measures against those 
organizations that are defined as terrorist in nature, their 
members, and their property, with all the attendant 
ramifications. 

</TEXT>

