<H3> <TI>   Russian Foreign Minister Holds Talks With Rabin </TI></H3>
<H4>   Rabin to Kozyrev: Coordinate With U.S. </H4>
<F P=102> TA1103164794 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1600 GMT 11 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1103164794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] In a meeting with the Russian foreign minister 
in Tel Aviv today, the prime minister implied that he was 
dissatisfied with Russia's independent involvement in the peace 
process without coordination with the United States. The peace 
process cosponsors -- Russia and the United States -- will do 
well to coordinate their positions, Mr. Rabin told Andrey 
Kozyrev. 
  He reiterated the Israeli stand that there is no point in 
reopening signed agreements, and that the PLO should return at 
once to the negotiations with Israel. Our political 
correspondent Shlomo Raz notes that the visiting statesman 
called on Israel to make a move that will persuade 'Arafat. 
  The meeting, which was held in the prime minister's Tel Aviv 
office, was also attended by Major General Amnon Shahaq, head of 
the Israeli delegation to the Taba talks, and Shim'on Sheves, 
director general of the Prime Minister's Office. [passage 
omitted] 

