<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Team Leaves for Tunis for Talks With 'Arafat, Ross </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1403053094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0500 GMT 14 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1403053094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] An Israeli delegation is leaving for Tunis for 
talks with Yasir 'Arafat and Dennis Ross, the U.S. official 
responsible for the peace negotiations. Ross arrived in the 
Tunisian capital yesterday. The Israeli team is made up of the 
director general of the Foreign Ministry, Uri Savir; General 
'Uzi Dayan of the IDF [Israel Defense Forces]; and the prime 
minister's political adviser, Jacques Neriya. 
  The decision to dispatch the delegation to Tunis came in the 
wake of the intensive American efforts to bring about renewal of 
negotiations between Israel and the PLO. 
  Qol Yisra'el's Washington correspondent says also that 
Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres and the PLO's Abu-Mazin [Mahmud 
'Abbas] are likely to meet at the end of the week to restart 
talks on the autonomy for Gaza and Jericho. The Washington 
meeting is apparently dependent on the outcome of the contacts 
now under way in Tunis. 

</TEXT>

