<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   More Arab Workers Permitted Into Israel </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1303135894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1300 GMT 13 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1303135894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Despite the closure on the territories, the number 
of workers who have received permits to enter Israel has 
recently been increased. Officials at the Employment Service 
told our correspondent Ya'el Ayalon that over the weekend, 
another 5,300 workers were issued permits, bringing the total 
number of agricultural and industrial workers from the 
territories with permits to work in Israel to 9,800. From now 
on, all workers from the territories over the age of 30 will be 
eligible for a work permit on the condition that they are 
married. 

</TEXT>

