<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Khamene'i Issues Statement Ending Ramadan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1203195894 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1930 GMT 12 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1203195894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The following statement was released by the esteemed 
leader's office on observation of the crescent of the month of 
Shawwal: 
  In the Name of God, the Compassionate, the Merciful. May God 
accept the religious duty of fasting and prayers by all Muslim 
brothers and sisters. By congratulating the auspicious feast of 
Id al-Fitr to world Muslims, particularly to the dear nation of 
Iran, it is hereby announced that, according to reliable 
reports, the crescent of the month of Shawwal has been seen in 
Khuzestan and Esfahan Provinces. The esteemed leader, His 
Eminence Ayatollah Khamene'i, is certain that the month of 
Shawwal has begun. Tomorrow, 13 March, is herefore the first of 
Shawwal and the auspicious feast of Id al-Fitr; and the glorious 
Id al-Fitr prayers will be held all over the country tomorrow 
morning. 
  [Signed] The esteemed leader's office. 

</TEXT>

