<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Condemns UN Human Rights Resolution </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1103172594 Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network in 
Persian 1530 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1103172594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Islamic Republic of Iran's Foreign Affairs 
Ministry issued a statement today describing the action taken by 
the UN Human Rights Commission as irresponsible and strongly 
condemned it. 
  In a vote, the UN Human Rights Commission, despite the fact 
that the majority of its members voted against or abstained, 
approved a resolution on the violation of human rights in Iran, 
supported only by Western countries. 
  The statement by the Islamic Republic of Iran's Foreign 
Affairs Ministry stresses: Those who issued the resolution have 
remained silent in the face of the Zionist regime's crimes at 
the al-Khalil mosque and have even stopped, in the first round 
of its debate, a resolution that would have condemned the 
Zionist regime. 
  The Foreign Affairs Ministry statement also mentions: It has 
been proved to the world that the Western countries who support 
such resolutions, are themselves practically assisting the 
anti-human crimes and the clear violation of human rights in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, in the heart of Europe, through their 
deception. 
  The statement by the Foreign Affairs Ministry of the Islamic 
Republic of Iran emphasizes that the Iranian punishment laws are 
based on the Islamic legal concepts, accepted and respected by 
over 1 billion world Muslims, and such resolutions not only have 
no credibility or legitimacy, but will also damage the 
credibility of such forums. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

