<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Candidate Proposed for Next OPEC Secretary General </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1403103594 Tehran IRNA in English 0835 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1403103594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, March 14, IRNA -- Iran's representative to 
the OPEC board of governors, Hoseyn Kazempur Ardebili, has been 
proposed for the post of the secretary general of the 
organization. The three-year term of the present OPEC secretary 
general, Ahmad Subroto, is to terminate in the next few months. 
  The new secretary general will be elected in next OPEC 
session to be held in Vienna on March 25. 
  According to the oil minister, Gholamreza Aqazadeh, if a 
rotating policy is adopted, it will be Iran's turn to chair the 
organization. However, he added, in case an alphabetic order is 
followed, the representative of Algeria would be elected. 
  Kazempur Ardebili is presently Iran's ambassador in Tokyo 
and 
is an expert in international oil policy. He has cooperated 
with OPEC for nine years as Iran's representative. He has also 
served as deputy oil minister for international affairs and head 
of the National Iranian Oil Company (NIOC) for two years. 
  Meanwhile, Venezuela and Algeria have also proposed their 
candidates for the post. 

</TEXT>

