<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Open-Fire Instructions Clarified </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1203173594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1700 GMT 12 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1203173594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Military sources have said that yesterday the IDF 
[Israel Defense Forces] took steps toward clarifying the 
open-fire instructions in the territories. Speaking to our army 
affairs correspondent Karmela Menashe, the sources said the 
steps were designed to prevent confusion among soldiers caused 
by a Border Police officer's testimony before the Shamgar 
Commission. 
  Our correspondent notes that the steps are designed to 
elucidate the existing instructions, according to which weapons 
are not to be used when enforcing law and public order on 
Israelis in the territories. Nevertheless, when observing an 
Israeli civilian shooting to hit others, or endangering others' 
lives without being in a life-threatening situation himself, the 
soldiers have to take every reasonable measure, including the 
use of firearms. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

