Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the press review] </F>
  [Text] Discussing the UN Security Council's deliberations 
on the Hebron massacre, AL-BA'TH writes in its "With the Events" 
column: 
  Awaiting a UN Security Council resolution and following 
world 
demand for an Israeli withdrawal and the implementation of the 
Geneva Conventions on the protection of civilians in time of 
war, the threats to peace, posed by the Ibrahimi Mosque 
massacre, have not gone away. Nor will the massacre lose its 
influence on the credibility of the UN Security Council, which 
is still holding consultations as if the massacre were less 
significant than Lockerbie or less vicious than the reasons that 
prompted UN troops to land in more than one capital of the 
post-Cold War world. 

</TEXT>

