<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Vatican Envoy: Church Bomb To Protest Israel Ties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1503072394 (Clandestine) Radio Free Lebanon in Arabic 0545 
GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1503072394 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Free Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A pro-Vatican magazine has quoted a Vatican diplomat 
as saying that there is a possibility that the bombing of the 
Sayyidat al-Najat Church [on 27 February] was perpetrated to 
protest the establishment of diplomatic relations between the 
Vatican and Israel. The Vatican diplomat revealed that the Holy 
See received signals in December that an attack against a 
Christian target in the Middle East was inevitable. He added: 
We feared attacks against Christian targets in the Middle East. 
He noted that the earliest signs of such a possibility emerged 
around Christmas, when the agreement between the Vatican and the 
State of Israel was signed. 

</TEXT>

