<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aborted Border Raid To Avenge Hebron Killings </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1203173394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1600 GMT 12 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1203173394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] SLA [South Lebanese Army] soldiers captured a lot 
of equipment in a pre-dawn clash with Popular Front terrorists, 
in which two were killed and two captured. The commander of the 
area said the weapons included grenades and explosive charges. 
They also had leaflets saying they had come to avenge the 
Hebron massacre. [Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew at 1600 GMT 
on 12 March adds that "the leaflets also specified terms of 
negotiations, in which the terrorists had planned to involve the 
French ambassador in Israel."] 
  The commander added that there had been an increase of 
terrorist activity in south Lebanon, and the wave of terror had 
reached its peak. 
  The gang was on its way to an attack on one of the northern 
border settlements. SLA soldiers noticed the band near Har Dov. 
In an initial clash, one terrorist was wounded and captured and 
three others escaped. Later, one of them surrendered to UNIFIL 
[UN Interim Force in Lebanon]. The other two were killed after 
a chase. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

