<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aswan-Cairo Train Fired Upon; Passengers Unharmed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1203151194 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1452 GMT 12 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1203151194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 12 Mar (MENA)--A responsible security source 
at the Ministry of Interior today stated that unidentified men 
opened fire at train No. 85 from a field between the village of 
Bani Qurrah and al-Qusiyah city, Asyut Governorate. The train 
was heading to Cairo from Aswan. The source noted that none of 
the train's passengers was hurt in the incident. The train 
continued its trip to Cairo. 
  Police departments continue their efforts to arrest the 
assailants and the prosecution office has been notified to start 
an investigation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

