<F P=101> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   G-15 Summit Scheduled for 28-30 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1103162294 Delhi ISI Diplomatic Information Service in 
English 1517 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1103162294 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi ISI Diplomatic Information Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Official spokesman's statement dated 11.3.94"] </F>
  [Text] The resumed fourth summit of the G-15 will take 
place in New Delhi from March 28-30, 1994. There is agreement 
that for this summit, as it is a resumed summit, the rules of 
the quorum (2/3rds) shall not apply. It is expected that a 
number of these states will participate at the level of the 
heads of state/government, judging from the responses received. 
We should, therefore, be assured of a good attendance at the 
summit level. The preparatory meetings of the personal 
representatives and of the ministers shall be held on March 25 
and 26 respectively. This resumed summit is expected to include 
discussions on issues relating to the future course of the G-15 
in a fast-changing world. 

</TEXT>

