<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Foreign Mercenaries' Reportedly Killed in Kashmir </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1203153794 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1135 
GMT 12 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1203153794 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Direct involvement of Pakistani nationals and Afghan 
mojahedin into Kashmir militancy and taking over command of 
terrorist leadership to step up subversive activities in Kashmir 
Valley have been established with the arrest of several foreign 
mercenaries and nationals of Pakistan. This came to light 
recently when an advertisement in a local Urdu daily of Srinagar 
gave the list of foreign mercenaries belonging to its outfit 
killed in Kashmir in encounters with the security forces. 
According to the newspaper, of the list of 35 such mercenaries, 
at least 27 were Pakistanis, three from Afghanistan, two from 
Saudi Arabia, and one each from Bahrain and Algeria. 
  The Border Security Force [BSF] today found 10 bags of 
foreign currency worth crores of rupees from the Regal area in 
Samba Sector of Jammu region. A BSF spokesman told PTI the 
currency notes of countries like Pakistan, United Kingdom, 
United States, Iran, Saudi Arabia, and India were sealed in bags 
and left at different places in the area. The spokesman said 
this is one of the major successes of the BSF in its drive 
against international smugglers operating between India and 
Pakistan via Jammu border. 

</TEXT>

