<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Holds Meeting With Israeli Delegation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1403185894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1842 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1403185894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tunis, 14 Mar (MENA)--Palestinian President Yasir 
'Arafat met again tonight with the Israeli delegation led by 
Jacques Neriya, the Israeli prime minister's adviser, who 
arrived here earlier today. 
  This morning the Israeli delegation met with 'Arafat and 
held 
intensive talks with him. Yuri Savir, director general of the 
Israeli Foreign Ministry, and General 'Uzi Dayan, head of 
planning in the Defense Ministry, took part in the talks as well 
as PLO Executive Committee member Yasir 'Abd-Rabbuh; Abu-Ala' 
[Ahmad Quray'], head of the PLO's Economic Department; and Akram 
Haniyah, 'Arafat's adviser on the occupied territories affairs. 
  Following this meeting, the Israeli delegation telephoned 
Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin and briefed him on the 
results of the talks with 'Arafat. 
  The Israeli delegation arrived in Tunisia last night aboard 
a 
private Israeli plane but the Tunisian authorities refused to 
let it land. The delegation then returned to Rome where it 
boarded the plane that carried Dennis Ross, U.S. coordinator on 
the Middle East peace process, from Rome to Tunis. 

