<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ross, 'Arafat Meet; Ross Comments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1403201494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1946 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1403201494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tunis, 14 Mar (MENA)--PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat and 
Dennis Ross, U.S. coordinator on the Middle East peace process, 
held a closed meeting this evening. After the meeting, which 
lasted about 75 minutes, Ross said they discussed the PLO's 
commitment to resuming the peace negotiations and its commitment 
to the Declaration of Principles. He said they also discussed a 
number of topics, including Palestinian concerns about the 
situation in the occupied territories and commitments related to 
the peace process. Ross said that the most important thing is to 
finish these negotiations and start implementing the Declaration 
of Principles. What concerns us, he said, is to see a change in 
the situation on the ground, new realities in the region, and 
the implementation of the Declaration of Principles. 
  Before meeting with 'Arafat, Ross met with the Israeli 
delegation led by Jacques Neriya, the Israeli prime minister's 
adviser, who arrived in Tunis today. 

</TEXT>

