<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Sends Written Message to Yeltsin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1403180594 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1702 GMT 
14 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1403180594 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Voice of Palestine </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brother President Abu 'Ammar [Yasir 'Arafat] 
yesterday sent a written message to Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin in reply to his important political message conveyed by 
Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev to brother President Abu 
'Ammar the day before yesterday in Tunis. 
  In his message brother President Abu 'Ammar expressed his 
great satisfaction at the high level of cordiality and sincerity 
in the current dialogue between the PLO and friendly Russia, 
which confirms the standing and development of the relations of 
friendship, cooperation, and consultation between the 
Palestinian and Russian peoples. 
  Brother President Abu 'Ammar valued President Yeltsin's 
eagerness for the peace process and negotiations to continue, 
the important steps taken by President Yeltsin and the Russian 
Government to prevent the escalation of violence in the occupied 
Palestinian territories, and also Russian efforts in the UN 
Security Council in getting issued an effective resolution that 
would fulfill the Palestinians' just demands. 
  In his message brother Abu 'Ammar also expressed his 
confidence that friendly Russia, as a co-sponsor of the peace 
conference, would continue to make efforts to ensure the 
implementation of the Declaration of Principles agreement. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

