<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Pledges Revolution `Until Victory' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1403181394 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1702 GMT 
14 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1403181394 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Voice of Palestine </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yesterday morning brother President Abu 'Ammar 
[Yasir 'Arafat] visited the martyrs' cemetery in Tunis 
accompanied by members of the Palestinian leadership and 
revolutionary cadres. 
  After the brother president and those attending had recited 
Surah al-Fatihah [opening verses of the Koran] for the souls of 
the innocent martyrs, brother President Abu 'Ammar gave an 
address in which he stressed that the waterfall of Palestinian 
blood would not halt for one moment until the Palestinian flag 
and the flag of the Arab nation were raised over the walls, 
minarets, and churches of Jerusalem. 
  Brother President Abu 'Ammar made a pledge to all the 
martyrs 
that the revolution, on whose long and difficult road they had 
fallen, would continue, however great and long the sacrifices 
and however much the difficulties increased, through the 
determination and will of our people until victory and as far as 
Jerusalem. 

</TEXT>

