<H3> <TI>   Uzbekistan To Open Embassy in Tehran in Apr </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1403144894 Tehran IRNA in English 1332 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1403144894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, March 14, IRNA -- Uzbekistan is to open its 
embassy in Tehran early in April, Uzbek Deputy Foreign Minister 
Murad Khakimov told Iran's ambassador Mohammad-Musa Hashemi 
Golpayegani in Tashkent Monday. Khakimov also named Parviz 
Aliyev as Uzbekistan's temporary charge d'affaires to Tehran, 
and said Aliyev would be in Tehran to open the embassy. 
  The two officials discussed promotion of mutual relations, 
establishment of a direct air link between Tehran and Tashkent 
and setting up of a joint economic commission. 

</TEXT>

