<H3> <TI>   Abadan Airport Resumes Flights To Dubayy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1403112594 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1030 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1403112594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The first flight abroad from Abadan's 
international airport took off this morning. After 13 years of 
interruption the airport resumed its international flights as 
the first plane left Abadan for Dubayy. There are two weekly 
return flights by the Aseman [Sky] airways to Dubayy on Mondays 
and Fridays, carrying 80 passengers in each flight. 
  Two return flights from Tehran to Abadan are also added to 
the [Aseman] domestic flights. These flights are also scheduled 
for Mondays and Fridays so as to assist the passengers in 
Abadan. This brings the total number of Aseman airways return 
flights from Tehran to Abadan to three flights per week. 
[passage omitted] 

