<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Gives Statistics on Steel Exports </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1403145694 Tehran IRNA in English 1103 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1403145694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, March 14, IRNA -- Iran exported over dlrs. 
310 million worth of steel within the past 11 months, said an 
official of National Iranian Steel Company here Monday. Musa 
Aqa'i Lankarani, the company's plan and project deputy, told 
IRNA that one million tons of steel products had also been 
exported over the current year. Pointing out that Iranian steel 
was highly demanded by world market for being produced of best 
raw materials, Lankarani remarked that China, Thailand, 
Phillipine and Taiwan were among the purchasers of the Iranian 
steel. 
  Iran would also export its steel to the Persian Gulf Arab 
states in the near future, he continued. He further noted that 
the plan for the development of steel industry in Iran was under 
serious study, saying that Iran was planning to increase the 
capacity of its existing steel units. 
  According to Lankarani, two steel plants with the annual 
capacity of 350,000 and 550,000 tons each would be established 
in the northeastern province of Khorasan and northwestern 
province of Azarbaijan in future. On privatization policies, 
the deputy commented that the trend had begun since two years 
ago and that so far more than 10 units had been transferred to 
the private sector. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

