<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Esfahan-Yazd Gas Pipeline Project Completed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1303181894 Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network in 
Persian 1730 GMT 13 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1303181894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The project of laying 318 km of gas pipelines from 
Esfahan to Yazd has been completed. According to a report from 
our correspondent, this pipeline comprises two separate 
sections, which start from Kuhpayeh, and after crossing the 
regions of Na'in, Haqda, Ardakan, Meybod, Ashk-e Zar, and Zarch 
reaches the city of Yazd. 
  The Housing Development of the Oppressed and the War 
Disabled 
Foundation of the Islamic revolution completed this project 
under the supervision of the Iranian National Gas Company at the 
cost of 8 billion rials and 20 million dollars in hard currency. 

</TEXT>

